@mcjjin I am assuming you are using a 64-bit python distribution. If for now you want to have TensorFlow going while the issue is addressed seeing if the problem is with the wheel, please try:
pip install tensorflow

edit: @mcjjin my mistake about this suggestion. I don't know why for some reason I would assume PYPI whl is a different build from the provided on tensorflow.org. I suspected the distribution would be the problem for you also but thought about trying the above first. Glad you solved.
